<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-F7936095-9442-4058-9F8E-004B317DD3F1" version="2" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-F7936095-9442-4058-9F8E-004B317DD3F1" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Service workflow on the system</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">Hereby the overview of the steps on the system to do a service visit. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-99420987-624D-4DD0-B347-3BB55E0CF5B9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview</title><fig id="GUID-D0DA7752-A221-43A1-95EC-2FA149A8202A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-57BA8F5F-349F-440B-9B3F-7B347CA8E65C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-57BA8F5F-349F-440B-9B3F-7B347CA8E65C-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-75ED8483-7005-4890-9996-7F24DE6498C5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remark 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Analyze the customer complaint with ADAM / TSM / SDS. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows controller ON (ADAM &amp; TSM usable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Engine ON (SDS usable) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p><note id="GUID-03971AF6-5020-4F17-B67C-C4D57AFB137C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The system will generate several error codes. Example: 22500xx Unexpected power loss .... 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows controller ON (ADAM &amp; TSM usable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Engine ON (SDS usable) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fix a hardware issue while safely using the TSM on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows controller ON (ADAM &amp; TSM usable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Engine OFF (Safe repair). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">* 
</p><note type="caution" id="GUID-0B09D55F-24BC-459B-ACFD-6DCEDE9C7A3E" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The Power box is still connected to the mains supply !!! 
</p></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows controller ON (ADAM &amp; TSM usable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Engine ON (SDS usable) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Wait until engine is ready to test the fix. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows controller ON (ADAM &amp; TSM usable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Engine ON (SDS usable) 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-E12C24D6-6EBE-449B-8AD1-0EF35B02667B" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">When to use the Service jumper (22X6)</title><p class="- topic/p ">It is allowed to remove the service jumper in the following situations: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The system is in Cold SDS 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The system is in an MRE situation (Operator panel shows 'system error'). 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-B7333C89-8721-4DA9-9E0D-1EA392C47028" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Why using the Service jumper</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Service jumper enables the service technician to safely repair while using the TSM documentation on the operator panel. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Furthermore, it is much faster to keep the windows controller on and only switch the engine off and on again. This saves time during the service visit. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-A46E2920-A4BD-47F0-93C5-D53305F6B933" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Where is the Service jumper (22X6)</title><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="22COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F9B91945-CB0C-4E4A-AFEB-0B62B0D1872C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 22 The components of Power?>22 The components of Power</xref> for the location
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-999A1101-A86D-4115-B1B1-9B486EABF826.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
